          "title": "Elasticache Serverless settings",
          "helpText": {
            "aws": "With ElastiCache Serverless you pay for data stored in the cache and the requests you execute on the cache. <br><br> <b>Data stored:</b><p> You pay for data stored in ElastiCache Serverless billed in gigabyte-hours (GB-hrs). ElastiCache Serverless continuously monitors the amount of data stored in your cache, sampling multiple times per minute, and calculates an hourly average to determine the cache’s data storage usage in GB-hrs.</p> <b>Note:</b> Each ElastiCache Serverless cache is metered for a minimum of 1 GB of data stored.<br><br> <b>ElastiCache Processing Units (ECPUs):</b> You pay for ElastiCache Serverless requests in ElastiCache Processing Units (ECPUs), a unit that includes both vCPU time and data transferred. Reads and writes require 1 ECPU for each kilobyte (KB) of data transferred. For example, a GET command that transfers 3.2 KB of data will consume 3.2 ECPUs. Commands that require additional vCPU time or transfer more than 1 KB of data will consume proportionally more ECPUs. <p>In this calculator you can provide the average request rate (per second or or per hour) that you expect to execute on the cache and the estimated data transferred per request. We will use this to calculate your estimated ECPU costs. </p> <b>Note:</b> There’s no minimum metering for ECPUs. <br/> <p>Learn more about ElastiCache Serverless pricing and see pricing examples <a href='https://aws.amazon.com/elasticache/pricing/'>here.</a></p>",
            "aws-cn": "With ElastiCache Serverless you pay for data stored in the cache and the requests you execute on the cache. <br><br> <b>Data stored:</b><p> You pay for data stored in ElastiCache Serverless billed in gigabyte-hours (GB-hrs). ElastiCache Serverless continuously monitors the amount of data stored in your cache, sampling multiple times per minute, and calculates an hourly average to determine the cache’s data storage usage in GB-hrs.</p> <b>Note:</b> Each ElastiCache Serverless cache is metered for a minimum of 1 GB of data stored.<br><br> <b>ElastiCache Processing Units (ECPUs):</b> You pay for ElastiCache Serverless requests in ElastiCache Processing Units (ECPUs), a unit that includes both vCPU time and data transferred. Reads and writes require 1 ECPU for each kilobyte (KB) of data transferred. For example, a GET command that transfers 3.2 KB of data will consume 3.2 ECPUs. Commands that require additional vCPU time or transfer more than 1 KB of data will consume proportionally more ECPUs. <p>In this calculator you can provide the average request rate (per second or or per hour) that you expect to execute on the cache and the estimated data transferred per request. We will use this to calculate your estimated ECPU costs. </p> <b>Note:</b> There’s no minimum metering for ECPUs."
          },
